snippet: Lawmakers could not agree on a plan for redrawing congressional districts to present to the State Supreme Court.
abstract: Florida lawmakers fail to agree on how to redraw congressional maps that state's Supreme Court has called unconstitutionally gerrymandered; House and Senate are expected to present separate versions of map, leaving court to determine next step.
lead_paragraph: Lawmakers could not agree on a plan for redrawing congressional districts to present to the State Supreme Court.

headline.main: Florida Legislators Fail to Agree on Congressional Districts
headline.print_headline: Florida Legislators Fail to Agree on Districts
